HEADWORD: Yote
<hw>Yote</hw> <pr>(y⟦omac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>⟦yogh⟧eoten</ets>, <ets>⟦yogh⟧eten</ets>, to pour, AS.
<ets>ge⟦oacute⟧tan</ets>. See <er>Found</er> to cast.]</ety> <def>To
pour water on; to soak in, or mix with, water.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My fowls, which well enough,⟦br⟧
I, as before, found feeding at their trough⟦br⟧
Their <qex>yoted</qex> wheat.</q> <rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>You</ent>⟦br⟧
